    Author: A Groves
Date created: 21/09/2009              
                      
 Description:   This procedure has been created from:
        1) msip_DataWhsePrimaryTransformation

        to populate all the tables needed for OpenAccess and the 
        Secondary transformation stages.

        The purpose of this work is to minimise the modules in Primary
        to enable the OpenAccess module to complete ASAP. OA is then 
        made available to the field while the Secondary module runs.

      It is called as follows:

      exec msip_DataWhsePrimaryTransformationPart1 'Openwork', 'PrimaryTransformationPart1'

                  
Amendment History               
-----------------               
                      
Date		Who			Description       
----		---			-----------     
04/02/2009  A Groves	Moved mstp_CommTranInitialDate to before
						mstp_PolicyTransactions due to dependency.

11/08/2009  M Cawood	Comment out the procedures mscp_UserAccessControlHistory
						and mscp_UserAccessControl_AS as no longer used in Warehouse.

21/09/09	A Groves	msip_DataWhsePrimaryTransformation split into:
						1) msip_DataWhsePrimaryTransformationPart1
					    2) msip_DataWhsePrimaryTransformationPart2
						Note that mstp_Commissions has its own Batch job step.
						This has been done to reduce execution time of each
					    transformation step to facilitate batch step retries.
  
02/07/2010  M Cawood	Remove following procedures to run after Open Access enabled:
						mstp_TransAgentSplitHierarchyHistory (moved to SecondaryTransformationPart1)
						mstp_AdviserHistory (moved to SecondaryTransformationPart1)

16/09/2010  A Harrison  Remove code as per Codes Package relating to 
						1) mstp_DropLists procedure 
						2) Zurich_Openwork_CodesAndDescriptions_Import DTS script

16/09/2010  A Harrison  Remove code as per Products package relating to:
						1) mstp_CodeProductCategory procedure
						2) mstp_CodeBIProducts procedure
						3) mstp_CodeProductGroup procedure
						4) mstp_CodeProductSubGroup procedure
						5) mstp_CodeRevenueCategoryCode procedure
						6) mstp_CodeReportingProductProvider procedure
						7) mstp_CodeProdProviderReportingXref procedure
						8) mstp_CodeReportingProductCode procedure

22/09/2010  A Harrison  Remove code as per Products package relating to (missed from updates on 16Sep10):
						1) zurich_Openwork_ProductHierarchy_Import DTS script

27/03/2017	A Groves	SR464996/CH16204. 
						1) Comment out redundant DTS scripts as part of the DTS to 
							SSIS migration project.
						2) Comment out the Delegates Access List Load as this is
							now a SSIS script with its own Main Batch job step.
						3) Comment out "Zurich_Openwork_ProductionAdjustmentData_Import"
							as this will be replaced by a SSIS script. This script
							has always been run monthly as part of the Month End
							procedure, so it never needed to be in the overnight
							batch in the first place.

21/12/2017	A Groves	SR496622/CH19947
						mstp_Expectation uses mstt_PolicyTransactions but previously,
						the latter was populated after the former. Thus, mstp_Expectation
						has been moved to the end. The issue came to light when a new Owl
						case did not create the smoothed agent splits correctly in the OA
						Pipeline because the case was not in mstt_PolicyTransactions and
						therefore the Comm Shape ID was not picked up as it was one of the 
						special case commission shapes with non-banded rounding. 
****************************************************************************/
