/*************************************************************************************************
     Program:   msip_DataWhseSecondaryTransformationPart2     
    Author: A Groves
Date created: 23/06/2008              
                      
 Description:   This procedure has been created from:
        1) msip_DataWarehouseBuild

        to populate all the tables needed after OpenAccess has been 
        made available to the seller community.

        The purpose of this work is to minimise the modules in Primary
        to enable the OpenAccess module to complete ASAP. OA is then 
        made available to the field while the Secondary module runs.

      It is called as follows:

      exec msip_DataWhseSecondaryTransformationPart2 'Openwork', 'SecondaryTransformationPart2'

                  
Amendment History               
-----------------               
                      
Date		Who			Description       
----		---			-----------     
23/07/2008  P.Robathan  Move all procs in mstp_PopulateReportingServicesTables into this proc.  
						This should avoid confusion about where procs are run. Add calls to
						msp_FranchiseABCLeague and msp_SellerABCLeague  
                        
16/02/2009  A Groves	Remove the Transition Issued Production (TIP) load and transformation
						steps.  This is because this data is loaded manually and does not
						need to be part of the daily batch.  Note that proc 
						"mstp_TransitionIssuedProduction" must stay in the Primary Transform
						because it adds to table "msdt_Adviser".
              
02/07/2010  M Cawood	Rename to Part 2. Pre-OA processing moved behind OA enablement now running
                        as msip_DataWhseSecondaryTransformationPart1.
                        
27/03/2017	A Groves	SR464996/CH16204. Remove redundant DTS scripts as part of
						the DTS to SSIS migration project.
**************************************************************************************************/

