	Mike Cawood - 20 January 2010
	Performance Improvements - processing overview: 

	a)  Two new parameters added: @Mode and @MovementsStartDate. @Mode has two run
		settings:
 
			'FULL': This triggers the full refresh of the msit_CommissionStatement
					table. The table is truncated and its indexes are dropped and 
					recreated after the insert. @MovementStartDate is not used here.

			'MOVE': In this mode only those S_AGMFIL and ReportBACSExport rows that 
					are linked to daily movements are processed. The primary keys of
					these movements are held on the owt_TransformationMovements table.
					The rows processed are deleted from the msit_CommissionStatement 
					table and then inserted from the new data generated by the procedure. 
					Indexes	are not dropped/created in this mode.

	b)	The procedure works upon a list of Staging Table ID's identified according to
		the @Mode specified. For a 'FULL' run this list will comprise every ID on the
		S_AGMFIL and ReportBACSExport staging tables. Results are stored on a temporary
		table #msit_CommissionStatement.

	c)  The data on the #msit_CommissionStatement table is then applied to the 
		msit_CommissionStatement table as per the @Mode (see above).

	Two further amendments have been made:
		(1) Add BACSExportID (new column) - populated with ReportBACSExport.ID - to
