	Alan Groves - 10 October 2014 SR323395
	This enhancement changes the calculation of ELITE points for Level paying group schemes from the 
	large, front loaded client's first payment, to a smaller drip on every payment. This change was at 
	the request of Marcus Cossey who - prior to this change - was applying adjustments manually in the
	league tables to reduce the excessive award of points that the front loading was giving.

	Alan Groves - 09/12/2014 SR350491
	The requirement for Owl matched payments is to set ELITE points to zero. Although we can customise
	the OpenAccess Commission Listing to not display ELITE points, the "Enterprise Performance Summary" 
	(first OpenAccess screen) shows ELITE and this screen can't be customised.		
	
	John Wilson - 20/04/2015
	"Upd #19" change the hardcoded rate of 1.25 to lookup the enhancement rate value from the 
	sa_swift_CodeCommissionShapeRateHistory table.
	
	Alan Groves - 30/04/2015 SR371343
	New ELITE points calculation introduced as requested by Mark Duckworth via Marcus Cossey. The new
	calculation is based on Openwork margin rather than amount paid to advisers on the basis that the
	higher the Openwork margin, the more ELITE points for the adviser. Note that the old rules will apply
	to all payments prior to commission month Jan 2015 and the new rules will apply to all payments
	from Jan 2015 onwards. The only change to the old calculation is to limit it to payments prior to Jan 
	2015. The new rules are coded in a separate update immediately following the original update.

	Alan Groves - 21/05/2015 SR380825
	The new ELITE calculation (where cs.MONTH >= '2015-02-01') was found to have a flawed "ELITE_Initial" 
	calculation where points awarded could be the opposite sign to the ABC value. In addition, incorrect 
	values could be calculated where the calculation went wrong due to double negatives. 
	The changes to the "ELITE_Initial" calculation are as follows:
	1) The special cases for -ve AMOUNT_REC were removed and the standard calculation modified
	   to handle -ves.
	2) The SINGLE and INDEMNITY payments were moved before the ACCRUALs and LEVELs.
	3) Defensive coding added to ensure that the result of the calculation doesn't go negative.
	4) If the SINGLE or INDEMNITY calculation does not get triggered, then processing will drop
	   through to the ACCRUALs and LEVELs as a second chance - hence no check for the FREQUENCY
	   or the PAY BASIS for these. This seems to work well. 
	5) Previously only protection used CommBaseAmount. This has been changed to also include 
	   commission-based COB (pensions and investments). 
	6) Treat IC Clawbacks and IC adjustments like SINGLEs and Indemnity. This is because INIssued
	   for these commission types is the indvidual adviser payment and not the whole amount
	   due. 	 
	7) Group pension schemes can be accrual and indemnity terms as well as Level, so remove the 
	   Level restriction.
	8) Restrict front-loading to just initial commission - not initial clawbacks or initial adjustments.

	Alan Groves - 21/07/2015 SR391101
	There is a bug in the original ELITE calculation where COB accruals should have calculated a 
	front-loaded ELITE figure - but didn't. Instead the ELITE calculation was derived on each 
	payment. This meant that when the 2015 ELITE rules started to apply - which correctly front
	loads accrual ELITE points - then the per-payment accrual calculation ceased. This meant that
	advisers missed out on part of their ELITE award. This fix ensures that where a COB accrual
	case issued before the 2015 ELITE rules applied, then the old ELITE rules continue to be used 
	throughout the period covered by the new rules.
	Thus, the old calculation has an additional WHERE clause to include COB accruals that would
	normally be covered by the new rules and the new rules calculation has a similar WHERE clause
	to exclude these. Finally, the ELITE_Category in the 2015 calculation is appended with "-2015"
	so it is clear which calculation has calculated the ELITE points.
	
	John Wilson - 22/07/2015
	"Upd #19" - The previous update of mine (20/4/15) used the transactiondate to lookup the enhancement value.
	It has since transpired that the proposaldate should be used. This change is to update that.
	Also, it has been requested that the commission value be 2 decimal places.
	
	Alan Groves - 04/09/2015 SR399355
	New "Upd #53c" to suppress payments from the OpenAccess Commission Listing or standing orders 
	from the OpenAccess Account Statement, where requested by the business. This suppression is
	config driven via table "owt_SelectionControl" and the effective dates on that table. 

	Alan Groves - 03/03/2016 SR423797/CR406. 
	New rules for the ELITE calculation on payments from 2016 onwards as follows:
	1)	Remove the 12 months stop rule
	2)	End old factors and multipliers config as at 2015 and create new config effective from 2016 
		with all factors and multipliers set to 1.
	3)	Create data fixes to retrospectively correct the 2016 payments already processed on the 
		following tables:
		a)	msit_CommissionStatement
		b)	msit_OpenworkAdviserListing
		c)	omst_OMSCommissionPayments
		d)	owt_PaymentshieldCommissionPayments
	 
	Chris Mellors - 17/04/2019
	Added Page compression

	Chris Mellors - 24/03/2020
	Altered data types on 3 #msit_CommissionStatement temp table columns, to fix join issues

*/

declare		@RowCount			int,
			@ProcessMessage		varchar(100)

--MPC:21/01/2010 New ProcessLog Start
declare		@PhaseStart				varchar(50),
			@PhaseEnd				varchar(50),
			@PhaseLog				varchar(50),	-- AG 12/03/2014
			@ProcName				varchar(100),
			@ProgressModule			varchar(50),
			@OwlManager2Code		nvarchar(10)	-- AG 09/12/2014

set @ProcName		= object_name(@@procid) + ' - ' + @Mode
set @PhaseStart		= 'START'
set @PhaseEnd		= 'END'
set @PhaseLog		= 'LOG'
set @ProgressModule = 'CSTMT'

set @OwlManager2Code = (select cde.Code from msit_MIWarehouseCodesAndDescriptions cde	-- AG 09/12/2014
			where cde.ColumnName = 'Manager2Code' and cde.Description = 'Owl Financial')

exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseStart, @ProcName, null, @Module, @Client
--MPC:21/01/2010 New ProcessLog End

/*===========================================================================================
    IDENTIFY S_AGMFIL Rows to be Processed based on @Mode and @MovementStartDate
===========================================================================================*/

--MPC 21/01/2010 Start of Identify Payment Movements processing

CREATE TABLE #AGMFILChanges (ID int)
CREATE INDEX #X ON #AGMFILCHANGES (ID)

IF @Mode = 'FULL'	--FULL Reload of Table
BEGIN

	Insert INTO #AGMFILCHANGES
	Select Distinct ID 
	from sa_swift_S_AGMFIL 

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = 'FULL - IdentifyPaymentMovements : Count = ' + convert(varchar(10), @RowCount)		
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcessMessage, null, @ProgressModule, @Client

END	--@Mode = 'FULL'

IF @Mode = 'MOVE'	--Process Movements only
BEGIN

	Insert	INTO #AGMFILCHANGES
	Select	DISTINCT PKID 
	FROM	owt_TransformationMovements
	Where	DriverTableName = 'sa_swift_S_AGMFIL'
	and		CommissionStatement = 'Y'				-- AG 30/03/2010

	select @RowCount = @@rowcount
	set @ProcessMessage = 'MOVE - IdentifyPaymentMovements : Count = ' + convert(varchar(10), @RowCount)		
	exec msp_ProcessLog @PhaseEnd, @ProcessMessage, null, @ProgressModule, @Client

END		--@Mode = 'MOVE'

--MPC 21/01/2010 End of Identify Payment Movements processing

/*===========================================================================================
    PROCESS S_AGMFIL Rows selected based on @Mode and @MovementStartDate
===========================================================================================*/

--All columns except ID selected onto #msit_CommissionStatement as Primary Key defined on Insert

select
[AgentCode], [PaymentType], [StandingOrderCode], [StandingOrderDesc], [StandingOrderText], 
[CommissionType], [JournalEntryCode], [JournalEntryDesc], [ReportingClassCode], 
[ReportingClassDesc], [BusinessCode], [SellerName], [FranchiseName], [CommProviderCode], 
[CommProviderDesc], [PaymentDate], [BACSDate], [PaymentStatus], [Amount], [DebitCredit], 
[ExtPolicyNumber], [ClientSurname], [ClientForenames], [ProductCode], [StartDate], 
[FrequencyCode], [FrequencyDesc], [Premium], [CommissionRate], [InitialPeriod], 
[FranchiseUpliftRate], [PayBasisCode], [PayBasisDesc], [CommSacrificeAmt], 
[CommSacrificePct], [AgentSplit], [FranchiseSplit], [CommFeeCode], [CommFeeType], 
[CommReason], [TotDue], [FirstID], [LastID], [ExpectCount], [TotPaid], [AccruedToDate], 
[BaseAmount], [UpliftAmount], [EnhancementRate], [INIssued], [INAccrued], 
[INStilltoAccrue], [INIndemnity], [EXIssued], [EXAccrued], [EXStilltoAccrue], 
[EXIndemnity], [DistributorRef], [DueDate], [AuthDate], [PaidListDate], [AgentPaymentsID], 
[PendingPaymentID], [ExpectationID], [TransactionID], [PolicyID], [ClientID], 
[CommissionsID], [AgtStandingOrderID], [CaseID], [APE], [CreateDate], [Month], -- [ID], 
[ProviderName], [ProviderCode], [SuspendComm], [CommShapeID], [LastAccrualinMonth], [OAStatus],		--MPC:16/04/08 SR9 
[ABCValue],[ABCRate],[SchemeNum],[BACSExportId] 	--MPC: 21/01/2010		--PR:16/3/09 and 13/05/08 ABC
,[ELITE_Initial],[ELITE_Ongoing],[ELITE_NSC],[ELITE_NSCFee],[ELITE_OMNIS],[ELITE_OMNISRatio],[ELITE_Category]		--SR207107: MPC 11/03/2013
into	#msit_CommissionStatement
from	msit_CommissionStatement		--MPC:21/01/2010
where	1=0
