CREATE procedure [dbo].[mspr_FranchiseDataCheck]
 @Franchise  nvarchar(20),
 @Openwork  bit,
 @Statement bit,
 @Output bit OUTPUT
as
--########################################################################
-- Copyright (c) MOORE STEPHENS, 2002 All rights reserved
--
-- Object  : procedure
-- Name    : mspr_NSOrder.sql
-- Owner   : MWA
-- Created : 25/07/2006
--
--       14/02/2007  - RH/OW - Tuned for performance as part of Agent KPI report production issue
--         - Fixes to affected procs/fns include explicit conversion of datatypes in query
--           expressions where parameter type is not matched to table data type
--           allowing Index seeks rather than scans
--         - Addition of indexes to required Quality tables
--         - Explicit alternative logic paths for queries where global parameter (eg Filter) is not supplied
--           avoiding table/index scans forced by unnecessary OR statememnts
--########################################################################



Select @Output = 0

if (@Openwork = 1 AND @Statement = 1)
begin

if EXISTS ((SELECT top 1 BusinessCode  from msit_OpenworkBankDetails where BusinessCode = convert(nvarchar(7),@Franchise)) )
  Select @Output = 1
end
else if(@Openwork = 1 AND @Statement = 0)
begin

if EXISTS ((SELECT top 1 BusinessCode  from msit_OpenworkAdviserListing where BusinessCode = convert(varchar(7),@Franchise)))
  Select @Output = 1
end
else if (@Openwork = 0 AND @Statement = 1)
begin

if EXISTS ((SELECT top 1 BusinessCode  from msit_ZANBankDetails where BusinessCode = convert(nvarchar(7),@Franchise)))
  Select @Output = 1
end
else if(@Openwork = 0 AND @Statement = 0)
begin

if EXISTS ((SELECT top 1 BusinessCode  from msit_ZANAdviserListing where BusinessCode = convert(varchar(7),@Franchise)))
  Select @Output = 1
end

GO
